<paragraph blockId="157.[151,1437,898,1350]" pageId="157" pageNumber="158">
<emphasis box="[151,235,900,925]" italics="true" pageId="157" pageNumber="158">Leaves</emphasis>
veins raised and rectangular in cross-section adaxially; basal pinna 3.8(0.5–27.0) cm wide; apical pinna 6.4(1.5–15.0) cm wide. 
<emphasis box="[513,684,937,963]" italics="true" pageId="157" pageNumber="158">Inflorescences</emphasis>
prophyll margins with irregular, spine-like projections; flower pits usually spirally arranged, not distantly spaced.
</paragraph>
